{{Infobox games | name = I Pan American Sports Festival | logo = 2014 Pan American Sports Festival logo.png | size = 189px | caption = | host city = [[Mexico City]] | country = {{flagcountry|MEX}} | motto = | nations participating = | teams participating = | athletes participating = | events = | opening ceremony = | closing ceremony = | officially opened by = | athlete's oath = | judge's oath = | torch lighter = | stadium = | length = | indprize = | tmprize = | website = | previous = | next = }}
The '''I Pan American Sports Festival''' (Spanish: ''Festival Deportivo Panamericano'') was a multi-sport event held between 11 July and 30 September 2014 in [[Mexico]].<ref> {{ Citation | last = | first = | date = | title = Festival Deportivo Panamericano 2014 | url = http://festivaldeportivo.com/en/ | page = | publisher = | language = | accessdate = August 22, 2014 }} </ref> The Festival was organized by the [[Pan American Sports Organization]] (PASO).
==Venues== The Festival was held at various locations throughout [[Mexico]].<ref> {{ Citation | last = | first = | date = | title = Host Cities | url = http://festivaldeportivo.com/en/category/host-cities/ | page = | publisher = | language = | accessdate = August 22, 2014 }} </ref> {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center" |- ! City ! Venue ! Sport ! Date |- |[[Aguascalientes, Aguascalientes]] |Velódromo Bicentenario |Track Cycling |10–14 September |- |rowspan=2|[[Cuautlancingo (municipality)|Cuautlancingo]], [[Puebla]] |rowspan=2|Complejo Deportivo Cuautlancingo |Artistic roller skating |16–19 July |- |Roller speed skating |16–19 July |- |rowspan=4|[[Guadalajara]], [[Jalisco]] |rowspan=3|[[Complejo Nissan de Gimnasia]] |Artistic gymnastics |17–19 July |- |Rhythmic gymnastics |25–27 July |- |Trampolining |26–27 July |- |Complejo de Racquetbol de la Unidad Deportiva Revolución |Racquetball |2–8 August |- |[[Huauchinango]], [[Puebla]] |Río el Sifón |Slalom canoeing |11–13 July |- |rowspan=12|[[Mexico City]] |rowspan=2|[[Alberca Olímpica Francisco Márquez]] |Diving |27–30 September |- |Swimming |26–30 September |- |rowspan=2|[[Ciudad Jardín Bicentenario#Centro Deportivo|Centro Deportivo Olímpico Mexicano]] (CDOM) |Modern pentathlon |17–20 July |- |Synchronized swimming |27–29 September |- |rowspan=3|Centro Nacional de Desarrollo de Talentos Deportivos y Alto Rendimiento (CNAR) |Fencing |11–14 September |- |Table tennis |17–20 July |- |Weightlifting |19–21 July |- |[[Ciudad Jardín Bicentenario#Centro Deportivo|Estadio de atletismo Jesús Martínez "Palillo"]] |Athletics |15–16 August |- |Gimnasio Edel Ojeda, [[Instituto Politécnico Nacional]] (IPN), Unidad Zacatenco |Wrestling |15–17 July |- |[[Gimnasio Olímpico Juan de la Barrera]] |Boxing |16–20 July |- |rowspan=2|[[Xochimilco#Other landmarks|Pista Olímpica de Remo y Canotaje "Virgilio Uribe"]] (Cuemanco) |Canoeing |5–7 September |- |Rowing |17–20 July |- |[[Monterrey]], [[Nuevo León]] |[[Parque Fundidora]] |Triathlon |7 September |- |[[Pachuca]], [[Hidalgo (state)|Hidalgo]] |Centro de Convenciones TUZOFORUM |Judo |13–14 September |- |rowspan=2|[[Puebla, Puebla]] |Boliche Noria Pro |Bowling |17–20 July |- |[[Gimnasio Miguel Hidalgo]] |Taekwondo |19–21 July |- |[[Querétaro, Querétaro]] |Auditorio José María Arteaga |Badminton |13–15 September |- |rowspan=2|Tequesquitengo, [[Morelos]] |Playa Xoxo |Open water swimming |26–29 September |- |Pista de Esquí Acuático Aqua Ski |Water skiing |16–20 July |- |[[Tlaxcala, Tlaxcala]] |Pabellón commercial del Centro Expositor de Tlaxcala |Karate |26–27 July |- |[[Toluca]], [[State of Mexico|México]] |[[Universidad Autónoma del Estado de México]] (UAEM) |Archery |17–20 July |- |[[Zinacantepec]], [[State of Mexico|México]] |[[Gimnasio Juan Fernández Albarrán|Canchas de Squash de IMCUFIDE]] |Squash |7–13 September |}
