{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Athletics Association of Thailand |abbrev = AAT |logo = |logosize = |sport = [[Sport of athletics|Athletics]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = National |founded = {{nowrap|{{Start date and age|df=yes|1948}}}} |aff = [[International Association of Athletics Federations|IAAF]] |affdate = 1948 |region = [[Asian Athletics Association|AAA]] |regionyear = |headquarters = [[Khlong Luang District|Khlong Luang]], [[Pathum Thani Province|Pathum Thani]] |location = |president = {{nowrap|Pol.Col. Sant Sarutanond}} |chairman = |chairperson = |chair = |chiefexec = |vicepresident = |director = |secretary = Surapong Ariyamongkol |coach = |womenscoach = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = |year closed = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = http://www.aat.or.th/ |countryflag = THA |countryflag2 = |countryflag3 = |more = }} The '''Athletics Association of Thailand''' (AAT, {{lang-th|สมาคมกรีฑาแห่งประเทศไทย}}), officially known as the '''Athletics Association of Thailand under the Royal Patronage of His Majesty the King''' {{lang-th|สมาคมกรีฑาแห่งประเทศไทย ในพระบรมราชูปถัมภ์}}) is the national governing body for [[Sport of athletics]]. It is accredited by the [[International Association of Athletics Federations]] (IAAF) which is the governing body for the sport of Athletics in the world, and the [[National Olympic Committee of Thailand]] (NOCT). It founded in 1948.
The association is headquartered in [[Khlong Luang District|Khlong Luang]], [[Pathum Thani Province|Pathum Thani]]. The current head of the federation is Pol.Col. Sant Sarutanond.
