{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Clifton Park Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[York]], [[North Yorkshire]] | establishment = 1971 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = | club1 = | date = 23 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/866.html Ground profile }}
'''Clifton Park Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[York]], [[North Yorkshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1971, when the [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club|Yorkshire Second XI]] played the [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire Second XI]] in the [[Minor Counties Championship]]. The ground held its second and final Minor Counties Championship match the following year when Yorkshire Second XI played [[Cumberland County Cricket Club|Cumberland]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/866_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Clifton Park Ground]</ref>
Since 1984, the ground has played host to Yorkshire Second XI matches in the [[Second XI Championship]], hosting 20 matches to date<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/866_sec.html Second XI Championship Matches played on Clifton Park Ground]</ref> and 8 Second XI Trophy matches.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/866_set.html Second XI Trophy Matches played on Clifton Park Ground]</ref>
In 1973, the ground held a [[Women's One Day International cricket|Women's One Day International]] between [[Australia women's cricket team|Australia women]] and [[Jamaican women's cricket team|Jamaica women]] in the [[1973 Women's Cricket World Cup]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/866_wo.html Women's One-Day International Matches played on Clifton Park Ground]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, the ground is the home venue of [[York Cricket Club]]<ref>[http://www.yorkcricketclub.com/ York Cricket Club] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100823004721/http://www.yorkcricketclub.com/ |date=23 August 2010 }}</ref> who play in the [[Yorkshire Premier League]].
