{{Infobox Minor League Baseball |name = Dominican Summer League Braves |founded = |city = Boca Chica |misc = |logo = |uniformlogo = |class level = Rookie |past class level= |current league = [[Dominican Summer League]] |conference = |division = San Pedro de Macorís |past league = |majorleague = [[Atlanta Braves]] |pastmajorleague = |nickname = Braves |pastnames = |ballpark = Atlanta Braves Complex |pastparks = |leaguenum = 0 |leaguechamps = None |divnum = 0 |divisionchamps = |owner = Atlanta Braves |manager = Francisco Santiesteban |gm = }}
The '''Dominican Summer League Braves''' or '''DSL Braves''' is a [[minor league baseball]] team in the [[Dominican Summer League]]. The team plays in the San Pedro de Macorís division and is affiliated with the [[Atlanta Braves]].
==History== The team came into existence in 1989 and has been an independent Braves affiliate ever since, with only one exception. For the 1994 season, the team shared an affiliation with the [[Texas Rangers (baseball)|Texas Rangers]].<ref>https://www.baseball-reference.com/minors/team.cgi?id=b0d3660c</ref> From 2001 to 2005, the team split into two squads as DSL Braves 1 and DSL Braves 2, but became a unified team again for the 2006 season.<ref>https://www.baseball-reference.com/minors/league.cgi?code=DOSL&class=FRk</ref>
