{{infobox football tournament | name = FMF Cup | logo = | caption = | founded = 2000 | abolished = | region = [[Moldova]] ([[UEFA]]) | number of teams = 4 (since 2009) | current champions = {{flagicon|ROU}} [[Romania national under-17 football team|Romania U-17]] | most titles = | most successful club = | most successful team = {{flagicon|BLR}} [[Belarus national under-17 football team|Belarus U-17]], {{flagicon|ROU}} [[Romania national under-17 football team|Romania U-17]] (4 titles) | broadcasters = | motto = | website = | current = }} '''FMF Cup''' ({{lang-ro|Cupa Federatia Moldoveneasca de Fotbal}}) is annual [[association football]] friendly competition for junior national under-17 teams that take place in [[Chișinău]], [[Moldova]], since 2000. The traditional spring tournament are organize by the [[Football Association of Moldova]].
The first tournament was held in May 2000 in [[Chișinău]], and the winner was the Ukraine national under-17 teams.<ref>[http://newsmoldova.ru/sport/20120515/191415880.html Международный турнир на Кубок федерации футбола Молдовы пройдет в тринадцатый раз - ИА "Новости - Молдова"]</ref>
The tournament participants was divided into two group of four invited under-17 national teams. The winners of group play in the final, the second place teams play match for the 3rd place, the third team in group play match for 5th place. Since 2009 the teams played 3 round-robin 90-minute matches.<ref>[http://www.soccer.md/search/?action=search&query=%D0%BA%D1%83%D0%B1%D0%BE%D0%BA%20%D0%A4%D0%A4%D0%9C SOCCER.MD - ВЕСЬ ФУТБОЛ В МОЛДОВЕ]</ref>
